
### Step 4: Update `package.json` for GitHub Repository

Ensure your `package.json` points to your GitHub repository.

```json
{
  "name": "credit-card-validator",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "A simple npm package for validating credit card numbers using the Luhn algorithm",
  "main": "index.js",
  "scripts": {
    "test": "node test.js"
  },
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/yourusername/credit-card-validator.git"
  },
  "keywords": [
    "credit card",
    "validator",
    "luhn",
    "validation"
  ],
  "author": "Your Name",
  "license": "MIT",
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/yourusername/credit-card-validator/issues"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/yourusername/credit-card-validator#readme",
  "dependencies": {},
  "devDependencies": {}
}
